: Reputation means nothing</span><hr size=1> I am not happy at all with the Name Change for Dollars thing VI has come up with. <br>Besides what Stubble already wrote this could be an other bad scenario:-<br><br>1) Make sure you get very nice gear etc. of course with the help of your guild.<br>2) After you are all geared up, change the name of your character.<br>3) Tell all your guildies you *have to* quit because you are addicted, or something like that... <br>4) Ebay your character.<br>5) Return to EQ.<br>6) Hook up again with the unsuspecting people you screwed over and tell them you missed them sooo much you could not stay away…<br>7) Then rinse and repeat one more time<br>8) Move to new guild and/or server and start at 1.<br><br>I don't think this will happen a lot, most players are good people, but I do think it will happen.<br><br>~Coco<br> <p><p align="center"><a href="http://xavann.homestead.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://xavann.homestead.com/files/Coco/Coco.jpg" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/udrenthaod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DrenthAoD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Level 2, Generic Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 7:36:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fkanebaylecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=368.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Doesn't anyone else find it funny how everything Verant said they weren't going to do is now happening?<br><br>Oh, we can't allow players to switch servers! What about the dynamic economy!?! Name changes are bad, what about a player's reputation! Never going to happen!<br><br>I guess they gotta milk EQ for all it's worth before trashing it for SWG and EQ2. Fuckers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F